# Business documents are NOT tracked: binary PDFs bloat the repo, and GDPR erasure (Art. 17)
# must stay possible — git history is forever. project_memory/, ledger/ (text CSV), reports/
# and manifests ARE tracked. The folder-guide README.txt seeds ARE tracked — `dir/*` + negation,
# NOT `dir/` (git cannot re-include a file whose parent DIRECTORY is excluded; the dir/ form
# silently untracked the kit's own seeds and broke fresh clones).
inbox/*
!inbox/README.txt
archive/*
!archive/README.txt
outbox/*
!outbox/README.txt

# tooling artifacts
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# append-only hook/agent event log (diagnostic — never project state)
project_memory/.audit/

# GDPR data minimization: these carry counterparty/customer NAMES in target paths (a real
# deployment committed 140 customer names on day 1 — Art.-17 erasure impossible once in
# history). They stay on disk for the gates and operations; they stay OUT of git history.
# The ledger remains tracked: statutory bookkeeping retention overrides erasure there.
project_memory/filing_log.yaml
project_memory/migration_manifest*.yaml

# session-local kit bookkeeping (session_status owns these; per-machine state, never project state)
.claude/kit_last_seen_version
.claude/kit_update_pending.state
